author: wn.com
title: Retiring county judge expected to run for public defender
text: There is no one running to become the 4th Circuit public defender right now. But the retirement of the chief county judge in the Jacksonville-based circuit is likely to kick the dormant race into high gear by the end of the year. Chief County Judge Charles Cofer, 63, announced Wednesday that he would be stepping down from the bench Nov. 30. Cofer is expected to announce his candidacy for public defender soon after his retirement becomes official. read more ...
